{"questionId":"3475350","questionHtml":"<p>A 4.0 cm length of a conducting wire carries a current of 2.5 A. The length is parallel to another long straight wire that carries a current of 10 A. The distance between the wires is 1.0 cm. The currents are in opposite directions.</p>\n<p>What is the magnitude of the force and the direction of the force acting on the 4.0 cm length?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/cf5c6d9382d7b2b56523adc2b3bbd6d8282e1f80.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:515.922px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:23px;\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:23px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:219px;text-align:center;height:23px;\"> <strong>Magnitude of force / μN</strong>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:230.922px;text-align:center;height:23px;\"><strong>Direction of force</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:219px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">1.3</td>\n<td style=\"width:230.922px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">Towards other wire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:23px;\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:23px;\">&nbsp;B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:219px;text-align:center;height:23px;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width:230.922px;text-align:center;height:23px;\">Towards other wire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:22px;\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:22px;\">&nbsp;C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:219px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">1.3</td>\n<td style=\"width:230.922px;text-align:center;height:22px;\">Away from other wire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:25px;\">\n<td style=\"width:69px;height:25px;\">&nbsp;D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:219px;text-align:center;height:25px;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width:230.922px;text-align:center;height:25px;\">Away from other wire</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3475350","referenceCode":"EXE.1A.SL.TZ0.18","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A 4.0 cm length of a conducting wire carries a current of 2.5 A. The length is parallel to another long straight wire that carries a current of 10 A. The distance between the wires","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"18","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D. Fields","D.3 Motion in electromagnetic fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}